<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>Recall 97508 Rev. 1 - Accelerator Pedal Rod Breakage on 2000, 8100, and 8200 Series Truck Models and 3600,
        3800 Bus Models
    </stitle>
    <recall id="rec97508">
        <recallnumber>97508 Rev. 1</recallnumber>
        <market>U.S., Export</market>
        <recalldate>January, 1998</recalldate>
        <subjectfile>ENGINE</subjectfile>
        <subject>Accelerator Pedal Rod Breakage on 2000, 8100, and 8200 Series Truck Models and 3600, 3800 Bus Models
        </subject>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>2000
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>02/23/1997</startdate>
                        <enddate>04/01/1997</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>3000
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>10/28/1996</startdate>
                        <enddate>07/01/1997</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>8000
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>02/23/1997</startdate>
                        <enddate>04/01/1997</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <defect>
            <para>The accelerator pedal rod material is excessively brittle, and may break during a hard throttle
                application. Should the accelerator rod break, the engine would return to idle. The unexpected breakage
                could result in inability to properly accelerate the vehicle in a circumstance which
                <emph type="bold">could result in a vehicular accident without warning. This could result in personal
                    injury, property damage, or both.
                </emph>
            </para>
            <para>
                <title>MODELS INVOLVED (Revised Section)</title>
            </para>
            <para>In the recent recall, 97508, pertaining to the electronic accelerator pedal,
                <emph type="bold">some 2000 and 8000 Series vehicles were incorrectly identified that should not have
                    been in the recall.
                </emph>
                The following is the correct vehicle description
                <emph type="bold">of the vehicles involved</emph>
                in Safety Recall 97508.
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>2000 Series with Cummins N-14, Caterpillar, and Detroit Diesel engines built 2/23/97 through
                        4/1/97.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>3600 Model buses with the T 444E engine and I-6 electronic engines built 10/28/96 through
                        7/1/97.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>3800 Model buses with the I-6 electronic engines built 11/1/96 through 3/1/97.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>8100 Models with Cummins M11, Caterpillar, and Detroit Diesel electronic engines built 2/23/97
                        through 4/1/97.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>8200 Models with Cummins N14, Caterpillar, and Detroit Diesel electronic engines built 2/23/97
                        through 4/1/97.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <para>
                <title>OWNER NOTIFICATION</title>
            </para>
            <para>We apologize for this inconvenience and sincerely appreciate your efforts making the necessary
                corrections. A listing of owner names and addresses will have been furnished to the TSMs to notify
                dealers so the dealer can omit these VINs from the customer list. You must limit the use of this listing
                to this campaign since the list may contain information obtained from state motor vehicle registration
                records and the use of such motor vehicle registration data for purposes other than this campaign is a
                violation of law in several states.
            </para>
        </defect>
        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="2">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <para>The accelerator pedal rod can be replaced without removing the pedal assembly from the firewall.
                Please check the accelerator rod in the kit. If it is not the same rod size as the rod being replaced,
                <emph type="bold">do not change the rod</emph>.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using a Phillips head screwdriver, loosen one of the retaining screws on the retaining
                    plate. Back the screw out 5 to 7 turns (refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9750801">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9750801" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g9750501.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 1</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the second screw from the retaining plate. Rotate the retaining plate to allow
                    for the removal of the accelerator pedal and rod.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using retainer ring pliers (.069 tips), remove the pedal retaining ring.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the pedal, pedal bushings, and pedal spring from old rod.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">On the new rod, install pedal spring, and pedal bushings.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Before securing pedal to rod,
                            <emph type="underscr">make certain that the short end of the pedal is down and the
                                International logo is positioned correctly
                            </emph>
                            (refer to
                            <hotlnk xrefid="f9750802">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9750802" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g9750502.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 2</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure pedal to rod with new retaining ring.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install pedal and rod into housing, rotate retaining plate into position, and secure
                    with (2) retaining screws. Tighten both screws.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Test accelerator for normal operation.</para>
            </step1>
